.SH NAME
HTMLTableElement.tFoot \- HTMLTableElement: tFoot property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]HTMLTableElement.tFoot\f[B]\f[R] property represents the
\f[CR]<tfoot>\f[R] element of a \f[CR]<table>\f[R].
Its value will be \f[CR]null\f[R] if there is no such element.
.SH VALUE
A \f[CR]<tfoot>\f[R] element or \f[CR]null\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]if\f[R] (table.tFoot === myFoot) {
  \f[I]// \&...\f[R]
}
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
The interface implementing this property: \f[CR]HTMLTableElement\f[R].
